Add NestJS zero config support (#14009)

Adds NestJS support following same patterns as Hono and Express.
Previously, users had to specify the `vercel.json`:

```json
{
  "version": 2,
  "builds": [
    {
      "src": "src/main.ts",
      "use": "@vercel/node"
    }
  ],
  "routes": [
    {
      "src": "/(.*)",
      "dest": "src/main.ts",
      "methods": ["GET", "POST", "PUT", "PATCH", "DELETE"]
    }
  ]
}
```

Now NestJS works with zero config when tested with
https://docs.nestjs.com/first-steps. Testing with more complex projects
is still required.
